bio.experienceSummary: Hey yall, my name is Hadley! I have over 8 years of experience of caregiving with ages 6 months - 13 years old. One thing you can count on me, is making sure your home is cleaner than you left it :)
I have more than 15 years of experience caring for children ages 0-18. I taught English in Thailand to students ages 3-17. I have also worked multiple summer camps with children ages 4-18.

Hello! My name is QueenAmber, and I am a dedicated and experienced childcare provider with over five years of paid experience caring for children of all ages, from infants to pre-teens, including those with developmental disabilities. I earned my Bachelor's degree in Psychology from Spelman College in 2021 and am currently pursuing my goal of becoming a Physician Assistant.

I've always loved working with children, and I strive to create a nurturing, engaging, and safe environment for them. Whether it's assisting with homework, engaging in creative play, or ensuring a smooth bedtime routine, I tailor my care to meet each child's unique needs. I am also BLS certified through the American Heart Association.

I'm available to provide care in the evenings, on weekends, and occasionally overnight. I'd love the opportunity to support your family and care for your little ones!

description.displayText: We love her. My little one had no problem adjusting. Queen is dependable,  punctual, and great at adapting to my kid. I will continue to use her services and would recommend her.
description.originalText: We love her. My little one had no problem adjusting. Queen is dependable,  punctual, and great at adapting to my kid. I will continue to use her services and would recommend her.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi there! 
My name is Destiny and I'm 23-year-old college graduate from Georgia state university. I am:
- CPR certified 
- RBT trained (for the kiddos on the spectrum) 
- flexible with my schedule 
- a non smoker 
- happy, fun, and responsible 

Excited to work with you!

description.originalText: Destiny was completely terrific with my two young kids. Creative play, outdoor play, a sweet and peaceful spirit. Will definitely book again.

bio.experienceSummary:
I am a caring and experienced childcare provider with a passion for nurturing children's growth and development.

My calm and friendly demeanor creates a safe and welcoming environment for children of all ages. I have 3 years of experience caring for children from nannying an infant to student teaching in a child development center and am comfortable enforcing household rules.

With my educational background in Early Childhood Education, I bring a knowledge of child development to my caregiving and have experience with potty training. I'm also CPR-trained.

I enjoy engaging children in various fun activities, such as playing with their toys, educational activities, fun movement/exercise, and reading. I believe in open communication with parents and provide regular updates on their child's day. I'm also happy to help with cooking, meal preparation, carpooling, and housekeeping.

I'm committed to providing a positive and nurturing environment where your child can learn and grow safely!

description.originalText:
Rianna joined our family to watch our 4 month old baby girl last August. A friend referred her to us and noted her childhood development and childcare experience which we preferred our nanny have. Over the months we had Rianna in our home we watched our baby girl learn new things daily.  Rianna provided interactive play and a safe space for our little girl. She taught our baby sign language which was completely unexpected but amazing. We now have a 17 month old who has a vocabulary of over 150 clearly spoken words. Rianna definitely helped establish that knowledge. She also helped guide us in knowing appropriate developmental milestones. 

In terms of our working relationship, Rianna was friendly and social. She tidied up after herself and the baby. She was willing to help in anyway we requested and was cautious of the food allergies we live with. She communicates well with parents and family. She is extremely reliable and was always on time. 

We were so sad to see Rianna go but our baby started daycare shortly after Rianna graduated. That being said, Rianna stays in touch and has visited since moving away. Our baby still looks at her picture and says “Anna” regularly. We are so happy to have had Rianna in our home. She made a huge impact in our lives as first time parents and in our baby’s development.

bio.experienceSummary: Hey parents! My name is Vivica but everyone just calls me V for short. Recently, I just got out the military after serving 5+ years. I have been working with kids from a young age. Caring for siblings and cousins, which has made me extremely comfortable with babies and toddlers. I've worked at daycares and after school programs. I also have no problem engaging with older children. I feel that being in my 20s allows me to connect well with our younger generations. I do drive my own car, am comfortable with pets, and have my CPR/First Aid Certification. In addition to childcare, I can assist with housekeeping, homework, and family meal prep. I love taking kids to the park or interactive environments (with permission) to encourage fun and creativity. I believe in being highly adaptable, communicative, and passionate about creating a safe and creative space. Looking forward to hearing from you soon!

description.originalText: I have the chance of meeting Vivica as I was scouting for caregivers for my kids, me and Vivica met prior to her coming to my home so I can get a feel for her and get to know her. Vivica came to my home and she paired with my kids. She immediately took over with my 7 month, old son and she engaged with my seven year old daughter. Vivica is very sweet.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello, my name is Jada. I am currently pursuing a Master of Library Science degree, building on a strong foundation of experience and skills. During my undergraduate studies, I gained valuable experience babysitting for various families, caring for children ranging in age from 2 months to 14 years of age. 

In addition to babysitting, I also spent time as a summer school teacher, focusing on English Language Arts (ELA) for high school and middle school students. I currently work as a library specialist and love to dedicate my time expanding and growing minds!

I am always willing to work within families budgets and circumstances.

description.originalText: Jada was amazing! It was super last minute to try to find a babysitter and she was so understanding and she did great with my 4 yr old son

bio.experienceSummary: I graduated with a masters degree in mental health counseling from Georgia State University, and I spent the three years prior to grad school working   with 7th-12th graders. Before that as a high school and college student, I worked as a summer nanny for three years. I love kids and love the opportunity to support families in need of sitters.

Hello, 

My name is Kiana and I am a fun loving, hardworking, energetic, and responsible professor/writer from Alabama. I graduated with my MFA in Screenwriting from AFI in 2021. I will be on sabbatical from Cornell University from January to June and I am looking for a family I can work with for 6 to 9 months while I am escaping the Ithaca winter.

I was a nanny and household manager all through college and grad school from 2012 to 2021. I genuinely love children and typically choose to pick up nanny gigs in the summer when I am on break from teaching. I am super organized and very responsible. I absolutely love children. I have extensive experience with children who are special needs or preemies. Open to range of roles. I have over a decade of professional experience. I have been CPR certified over 8 times. I have references from my summer nanny gig last year in LA. I am reliable and I am looking for a family who is as well. 

Feel free to reach out. I'd love to connect.

description.originalText: Kiana was our nanny from 2012 to 2018. Ultimately we ended up moving her into a household manager role as well. She was integral in getting our schedules organized, a feat with four children. Originally, when we onboarded her, we had 2 school age children with various sports and activities. We were surprised with twins and that is when Kiana really shined. She is quick to jump into action and we realized she was meeting needs before we knew they were there. That coupled with her pleasant and professional demeanor is what led to her promotion. Kiana is great with children of all ages, and we were sad to see her go but very proud of her. We still use many of the implementations Kiana brought to our household, and we take every opportunity to see her when our schedules overlap. In addition to bringing balance into our homes, Kiana has become a part of the family.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi, I'm looking to partner with the right family to provide the most excellent care possible. I'm a 59-old retired mother of two adult children who are successful parents of their own. I take them to such places as the Fern-bank museum, the Puppetry Arts museum, zoo, story time, playgrounds and parks. I take great pride in what I do and want nothing more than to know that the children in my care are safe, happy and engaged.
